HEADWORD: citrin
<hw>citrin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a vitamin that maintains the
resistance of cell and capillary walls to permeation; -- called also
<altname>vitamin P</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> vitamin P, bioflavinoid.</syn>⟦br⟧
